reference_review:
POINTS:
- [modules/integration/src/test/java/org/apache/fluo/integration/client/FluoAdminImplIT.java:234] @kpm1985  I looked into this and found the problem.  The oserver object has an internal Environment object which caches the application ID from before the init.  To get around this, need to create a completely new Oracle Server. That can be done with the the following code.

```java
   //this will force reread of all info from zookeeper.
    Environment env2 = new Environment(config);
    OracleServer oserver2 = new OracleServer(env2);
    oserver2.start();
```

At the end of the test, can do the following :

```java
    oserver2.stop();
    env2.close();
```
- [modules/core/src/main/java/org/apache/fluo/core/util/CuratorUtil.java:119] This new method does not seem to be used.
- [modules/core/src/main/java/org/apache/fluo/core/client/FluoAdminImpl.java:215] This is a very nice check.  Could drop `You` from error message `Must stop the oracle server to remove an application`

